{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6236d858-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s395"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"395"},"text":"§ 395.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Leases of allotted lands where allottee is in­capacitated","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Whenever it shall be made to appear to the Secretary of the Interior that, by reason of age, disability, or inability, any allottee of Indian lands cannot personally, and with benefit to himself, occupy or improve his allotment or any part thereof, the same may be leased upon such terms, regulations, and conditions as shall be prescribed by the Secretary for a term not exceeding five years, for farming purposes only.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6236d859-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1900-05-31/ch598"},"text":"May 31, 1900, ch. 598","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/31/229"},"text":"31 Stat. 229","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6236d85a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6236d85b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id6236d85c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1900-05-31"},"text":"May 31, 1900","children":[],"tail":", is applicable to “any allottee of Indian 